  "text": "While deep seed dormancy and seed shattering are key traits for the survival of plants in the wild, these traits are not favorable for modern agriculture and are strongly selected against during crop domestication. Numerous studies have identified genetic loci or QTLs governing seed shattering in crop species, including rice [CITATION_1] . We analyzed the seed-shattering trait using a hybrid RIL from O. sativa/O. rufipogon.",
